# Modern CSS Best Practices

- Use CSS Grid for two-dimensional layouts
- Use Flexbox for one-dimensional layouts
- Implement proper responsive design with media queries
- Use logical properties (margin-inline, padding-block) for internationalization
- Use BEM methodology or similar naming conventions
- Implement CSS custom properties (variables) for theming
- Use CSS nesting when supported or with preprocessors
- Organize CSS with proper cascade and specificity management
- Use efficient selectors and avoid overly specific rules
- Implement critical CSS for above-the-fold content
- Use CSS containment (contain property) for performance
- Optimize animations with transform and opacity
- Use CSS logical properties for better internationalization
- Implement CSS custom properties for dynamic theming
- Use CSS aspect-ratio for maintaining proportions
- Leverage CSS clamp() for responsive typography
- Design mobile-first with progressive enhancement
- Use relative units (rem, em, %) instead of fixed pixels
- Implement proper responsive images and media
- Use container queries when supported
- Ensure sufficient color contrast ratios
- Respect user preferences (prefers-reduced-motion, prefers-color-scheme)
- Use focus indicators and skip links
- Make interactive elements large enough for touch
- Use CSS transforms for performant animations
- Implement smooth transitions for user interactions
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion for accessibility
- Use animation-fill-mode appropriately
